A clinostat system (3D clinostat, Shamhantech Inc., Bucheon, Korea), known as an effective system for simulating microgravity on the ground, was used in this study. This system is composed of two rotational axes and the rotation speed of each axis was fixed to 5 rpm (0.523 rad/s). These axes controlled each motors and drivers set (AiS-42MA, Autonics, Busan, Korea) (Suppl. Fig. S1A). The centrifugal accelerations of the system calculated by Eq. (1) were 0.0047 G (edge) to 0 G (center)46,47.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
